SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
Article – State Government
9–1A–06.
(a) [The] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN § 10–14A–03 OF THIS ARTICLE, THE
following persons shall be licensed under this subtitle:
(1) a video lottery operator;
(2) a manufacturer;
(3) a person not licensed under item (1) or (2) of this subsection who
manages, operates, supplies, provides security for, or provides service, maintenance, or
repairs for video lottery terminals or table games; and
– 6 –

WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 493
(4) a video lottery employee.
(c) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection OR §
10–14A–03 OF THIS ARTICLE, unless an individual holds a valid license issued under this
subtitle, the individual may not be employed by a licensee as a video lottery employee.
9–1E–05.
(a) [The] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN § 10–14A–03 OF THIS ARTICLE, THE
following persons shall be licensed under this subtitle:
(1) a person that operates sports wagering;
(2) a person that operates sports wagering on behalf of a sports wagering
licensee, including an online sports wagering operator;
(3) a person not licensed under item (1) or (2) of this subsection that
manages, operates, supplies, provides security for, or provides service, maintenance, or
repairs for sports wagering equipment and devices; and
(4) an individual directly employed in the operation of sports wagering by
a sports wagering licensee if the individual does not otherwise hold a valid license under
Subtitle 1A of this title.
SUBTITLE 14A. LICENSING – MEMBERS OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE AND SPOUSES.
10–14A–01.
(A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
INDICATED.
(B) “LICENSE” MEANS A LICENSE, PERMIT, CERTIFICATION,
REGISTRATION, OR OTHER LEGAL AUTHORIZATION REQUIRED FOR ENGAGING IN AN
OCCUPATION OR A PROFESSION.
(C) “LICENSING AUTHORITY” MEANS AN AGENCY OF THE STATE THAT
ISSUES A LICENSE.
(D) “MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS
EMPLOYED IN THE FOREIGN SERVICE OF THE UNITED STATES.
10–14A–02.
THIS SUBTITLE DOES NOT APPLY WITH RESPECT TO:
– 7 –

Ch. 493 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
(1) AN OCCUPATION OR A PROFESSION FOR WHICH AN INDIVIDUAL
WHO HOLDS A LICENSE ISSUED IN BY ANOTHER JURISDICTION STATE MAY PRACTICE
IN THE STATE UNDER AN INTERSTATE COMPACT; OR
(2) THE PRACTICE OF LAW.
10–14A–03.
(A) A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A MEMBER OF
THE FOREIGN SERVICE WHO RELOCATES TO THE STATE BECAUSE OF AN
ASSIGNMENT OR DETAIL TO THE STATE AND HOLDS A LICENSE ISSUED BY ANOTHER
JURISDICTION STATE MAY PRACTICE IN THE STATE UNDER THE LICENSE FOR THE
DURATION OF THE ASSIGNMENT OR DETAIL IF THE MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN
SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE:
(1) PROVIDES THE LICENSING AUTHORITY WITH A COPY OF THE
NOTIFICATION OF ASSIGNMENT OR DETAIL;
(2) REMAINS IN GOOD STANDING WITH THE REGULATORY AUTHORITY
THAT ISSUED THE LICENSE;
(3) REMAINS IN GOOD STANDING IN ALL JURISDICTIONS STATES IN
WHICH THE APPLICANT HOLDS OR HAS HELD A LICENSE OF A SIMILAR SCOPE OF
PRACTICE AND IN THE SAME DISCIPLINE;
(4) HAS ACTIVELY USED THE LICENSE DURING THE 2 YEARS
IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE RELOCATION; AND
(5) COMPLIES WITH THE STANDARDS OF PRACTICE, DISCIPLINE, AND
FULFILLMENT OF ANY CONTINUING EDUCATION REQUIREMENTS REQUIRED BY THE
LICENSING AUTHORITY.
(B) IF A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A MEMBER
OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE IS AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE IN THE STATE UNDER
SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION:
(1) THE MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A
MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE MAY PRACTICE UNDER THE LICENSE ONLY IN
THE DISCIPLINE AND TO THE EXTENT OF THE SCOPE OF PRACTICE WITHIN WHICH
THE LICENSE ALLOWS THE MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF
– 8 –

WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 493
A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE TO PRACTICE IN THE OTHER JURISDICTION
STATE; AND
(2) THE LICENSING AUTHORITY MAY NOT REQUIRE THE MEMBER OF
THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE
TO OBTAIN A LICENSE ISSUED BY THE LICENSING AUTHORITY UNLESS THE MEMBER
OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE
IS SEEKING TO PRACTICE IN A DIFFERENT DISCIPLINE OR WITHIN A DIFFERENT
SCOPE OF PRACTICE THAN THAT DESCRIBED IN ITEM (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
10–14A–04.
A MEMBER OF THE FOREIGN SERVICE OR THE SPOUSE OF A MEMBER OF THE
FOREIGN SERVICE THAT IS AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THIS
SUBTITLE:
(1) MAY PRACTICE TO THE SAME EXTENT AND IN THE SAME CAPACITY
AS AN INDIVIDUAL LICENSED BY A LICENSING AUTHORITY IN THE STATE,
INCLUDING SUPERVISING AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS LICENSED IN THE STATE WHO IS
REQUIRED TO PRACTICE UNDER SUPERVISION; AND
(2) IS SUBJECT TO THE SAME DISCIPLINARY AUTHORITY OF A
LICENSING AUTHORITY AS AN INDIVIDUAL LICENSED BY THE A LICENSING
AUTHORITY IN THE STATE.
10–14A–05.
EACH LICENSING AUTHORITY MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS
SUBTITLE.
Article – Agriculture
1–101.
(a) In this article the following words have the meanings indicated.
(d) “Department” means the State Department of Agriculture.
(i) “Secretary” means Secretary of Agriculture or [his] THE SECRETARY’S
designee.
2–301.
(a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
– 9 –

Ch. 493 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
(b) “Board” means the State Board of Veterinary Medical Examiners.
(c) “Direct supervision” means that the supervising veterinarian who is licensed
and registered in the State OR AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE IN
THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE:
(1) Is on the premises of the animal treatment facility;
(2) Is available on an immediate basis; and
(3) Has given written or oral instructions for treatment of the animal
patients involved.
(c–1) “Immediate supervision” means the supervising veterinarian who is licensed
and registered in the State OR AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE IN
THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE is in the
immediate area and within audible and visual range of the animal patient and the person
treating the patient.
(c–2) “Indirect supervision” means the supervising veterinarian who is licensed and
registered in the State OR AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE IN THE
STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE:
(1) Is not required to be in the same facility or in close proximity to the
individual being supervised; and
(2) (i) Has given written or oral instructions for treatment of the animal
patient involved;
(ii) Is available to provide supervision by electronic or telephonic
means; and
(iii) Has arranged for telephonic consultation with a licensed
veterinarian, if necessary.
(d) “License” means a license to practice veterinary medicine in the State.
(i) “Veterinary practitioner” means [a]:
(1) A licensed and registered veterinarian engaged in the practice of
veterinary medicine; OR
– 10 –

WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 493
(2) AN INDIVIDUAL AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY
MEDICINE IN THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
ARTICLE AND IS ENGAGED IN THE PRACTICE OF VETERINARY MEDICINE.
2–313.
(a) (2) A person may not:
(i) Practice veterinary medicine unless the person is [licensed]:
1. LICENSED, registered, and authorized to engage in the
practice under the provisions of this subtitle; OR
2. AUTHORIZED TO PRACTICE VETERINARY MEDICINE
IN THE STATE UNDER § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE;
5–207.
(a) (1) [Each] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN § 10–14A–03 OF THE STATE
